    "body" : "<p>Here are some of the easiest ways:</p>\n<h3><strong>In Kotlin:</strong></h3>\n<ol>\n<li><p><strong>Using <code>toString()</code></strong></p>\n<pre class=\"lang-kotlin prettyprint-override\"><code>val num: Double = 123.45\nval str = num.toString()\nprintln(str)  // Output: &quot;123.45&quot;\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>Using String Template (<code>&quot;$variable&quot;</code>)</strong></p>\n<pre class=\"lang-kotlin prettyprint-override\"><code>val num: Double = 123.45\nval str = &quot;$num&quot;\nprintln(str)  // Output: &quot;123.45&quot;\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>Using <code>String.format()</code> (For Custom Formatting)</strong></p>\n<pre class=\"lang-kotlin prettyprint-override\"><code>val num: Double = 123.456\nval str = String.format(&quot;%.2f&quot;, num)\nprintln(str)  // Output: &quot;123.46&quot;\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<hr />\n<h3><strong>In Java:</strong></h3>\n<ol>\n<li><p><strong>Using <code>String.valueOf(double d)</code></strong></p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>double num = 123.45;\nString str = String.valueOf(num);\nSystem.out.println(str);  // Output: &quot;123.45&quot;\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>Using <code>Double.toString(double d)</code></strong></p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>double num = 123.45;\nString str = Double.toString(num);\nSystem.out.println(str);  // Output: &quot;123.45&quot;\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>Using String Concatenation</strong></p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>double num = 123.45;\nString str = num + &quot;&quot;;\nSystem.out.println(str);  // Output: &quot;123.45&quot;\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>Using <code>DecimalFormat</code> (For Custom Formatting)</strong></p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>import java.text.DecimalFormat;\n\ndouble num = 123.456;\nDecimalFormat df = new DecimalFormat(&quot;#.##&quot;);\nString str = df.format(num);\nSystem.out.println(str);  // Output: &quot;123.46&quot;\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<hr />\n"
